        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2014-08-21 14:55:56.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2182 llite: Make setxattr behave like LOV_SETSTRIPE ioctl",
        "message": "LU-2182 llite: Make setxattr behave like LOV_SETSTRIPE ioctl\n\nWhile testing the layout enhancements as the back end to the\nlustre utilites I encountered some failures which I traced\nback to ll_setxattr. The first problem was several tests use\nlfs setstripe to change the first OST index to a specific\nvalue. That value was never being set due to ll_setxattr\nalways setting stripe offset to -1 in the case when stripe\noffset is set to zero. The second problem encountered was\nany error condition reported by ll_lov_setstripe_ea_info was\nbeing ignored. This is incorrect behavior which makes it seem\nlfs setstripe can be called multiple times on a file which\nreally is not the case.\n\nChange-Id: Idca8e23a9263d5a7fb4523719a2f25b80ce67462\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
